Continuous Delivery (CD) is more than automated deployments; it’s a cultural shift that emphasises frequent, reliable releases driven by metrics. Establishing a mature metrics program — tracking deployment frequency, change failure rate, lead time and customer satisfaction — helps teams identify friction and measure improvement. Research such as the DORA report correlates these metrics with business performance.

Organisations in Thailand adopting CD often see a reduction in time‑to‑market and improved quality. Investing in automated testing, infrastructure‑as‑code and pipeline observability ensures that teams can safely release multiple times per day. The goal is not speed for its own sake but faster feedback loops and happier users.

